        "timestamp": "2017-09-21 18:56:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nDan, It seems like sdnc-adaptors, sdnc-core, sdnc-plugins are placeholder repos now. Do we want jobs running at all on them?\n\nI see no problem removing release-1.0.0 however.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "90d5154ae70cbc745b71b8f49ac30b86ce6d73a6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-22 02:40:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI thought about getting rid of those, but I was worried that someone might still be using the 1.1.0 branch and didn't want to risk breaking their build (those staging versions tend to disappear, so the daily builds are really needed so they're not lost)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
